I’ve been to many countries. I had always thought that other countries were better than Hong Kong 🇭🇰 but after I’ve been to them I realise in terms of city life🏙nightlife🌃shopping🛍and food 🥘, Hong Kong is really the best. In Europe, shops 🏬 close at 4-5 on weekdays and don’t open at all at weekends except big cities like London where shops 🏬 close at 6 on weekdays and 4-5 at weekends. Their main sorts of entertainment are pubs and clubs.
Las Vegas has a spectacular night view but it was built primarily for tourism. It’s famous for gambling 🎰 unique hotel designs and shows like boxing events.
However, in terms of scenery, Scandinavia and Tibet are the best I would say. Tibet is famous for its breathtaking scenery at high altitude. Xinjiang is also a place of outstanding scenic beauty. In fact my friend who’s just been to Tibet showed me his photos by which I was awestruck. It’s a glamorous holiday destination. If you will have altitude sickness such as dizziness, headaches and trouble sleeping, I suggest bringing some medicine along. A tour of Tibet would be a once in a lifetime experience for many people. However if you ask me if Sydney 🇦🇺 is a great place to visit, I wouldn’t bet on it.

Tibet is also a marvelous place for stargazing 🔭 It’s much closer to the heavens than any other places on earth 🌏 it has some of the highest lakes in the world which are rich with fish 🐠🐟🐡and other marine life🦑🦐🐬🐳🦈and the surrounding countrysides are inhabited by flocks of yellow ducks 🦆 as well as wild horses 🐎 and donkeys. The lakes there such as Lake Paiku which is four thousand five hundred and ninety two metres above sea level, reflect the beauty of the stars ✨ giving a double view of the sky at night. You can pitch a tent 🏕 and camp there to get the best view of the stars and galaxies 🌌 Again, if you ask me whether Sydney is a great place to vacation in, don’t bet on it.
